genresAdvancedInfo.name: chinese metal
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Chinese metal is a heavy metal subgenre that originated in China in the 1980s. It features distorted guitar riffs, powerful vocals, and often incorporates elements of Chinese traditional music. Chinese metal bands often sing in Mandarin, making their music accessible to a wider audience.
